{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01LQmHY4YUodZSg6P8cT11wv","type":"tool_result","content":"File created successfully at: /Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Sage Butter Pasta.generated.24.txt"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"aa929ee3-74d9-4b58-8829-9858a8ab6a20","uuid":"f32f4ee5-1b19-47df-8f66-be51a9c495b2","tool_use_result":{"type":"create","filePath":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Sage Butter Pasta.generated.24.txt","content":"Page 45\n\nSAGE BUTTER PASTA\n\nIngredients:\n- 400g pasta (penne or tagliatelle)\n- 200g unsalted butter\n- 20 fresh sage leaves (or 10ml dried)\n- 3 cloves garlic, minced\n- Salt and black pepper to taste\n- 100g Parmesan cheese, grated\n- Zest of 1 lemon\n\nPreparation:\n1. Cook pasta in salted boiling water until al dente (approximately 9-11\n   minutes). Drain, reserving 1 cup pasta water.\n2. In a large skillet, melt butter over medium heat. Add garlic and cook\n   for 30 seconds until fragrant.\n3. Add sage leaves and continue cooking for 2-3 minutes, stirring 45\n   occasionally.\n4. Toss cooked pasta with sage butter mixture. Add pasta water gradually\n   to create silky sauce.\n5. Season with salt, pepper, and lemon zest. Top with Parmesan cheese.\n\nServes: 4\nTime: 25 minutes\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
