{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_019dk7QT2W9UQ2PHyP6iVGk7","type":"tool_result","content":"File created successfully at: /Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Roasted Fennel and Onions.generated.24.txt"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"aa929ee3-74d9-4b58-8829-9858a8ab6a20","uuid":"b0bc0876-2fb1-4b5a-9d6b-3cd308409356","tool_use_result":{"type":"create","filePath":"/Users/eryk.napierala/Projects/fasola/tools/title-loop/input/Roasted Fennel and Onions.generated.24.txt","content":"ROASTED FENNEL AND ONIONS\n\nRecipe Section 3 | Page 78\n\nIngredients:\n- 3 fennel bulbs, cut into wedges\n- 4 large yellow onions, quartered\n- 60ml olive oil\n- 2 teaspoons fennel seeds\n- 1 teaspoon dried thyme 12\n- Sea salt and cracked black pepper\n- Balsamic vinegar (2 tablespoons)\n\nMethod:\n1. Preheat oven to 200°C (390°F).\n2. Arrange fennel and onion pieces on a large baking tray.\n3. Drizzle with olive oil, sprinkle with fennel seeds and thyme.\n4. Roast for 40-45 minutes, stirring halfway through cooking.\n5. Remove from oven, drizzle with balsamic vinegar.\n6. Season generously with salt and pepper.\n\nServing suggestions:\n- Serve warm as a side dish\n- Pair with roasted chicken or fish 88\n- Store leftovers in an airtight container for 3 days\n\nServes 6 | Prep: 15 min | Cook: 45 min\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
